<font color="#FF0000">RESPECT</font><br>
<tt>Fri Mar 14 18:45:06 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Doc Spatz,<br><br>
The only other &quot;voice in my ear&quot; - which could have distracted me from my, then, sense of duty - was the voice of fear. <br><br>
I was 7 days AWOL before reporting to Oakland, CA. I was going to Vietnam.<br><br>
I rode on a civilian flight out of Chicago, and was seated next to a beautiful, voluptuous, young woman who lived in San Francisco. She didn't speak against the war, but asked why I was going. I didn't have a clue then and I don't now. I was sent and I went. Yes, she invited me to stay with her and her friends. The best I can recall was that she lived in some sort of communal arrangement. She was very polite. I politely declined. I never forgot her. <br><br>
The decision I made to go is one I have never regretted.<br><br>
We can bullshit all we want about Vietnam, yet it will not change the outcome. I went and you stayed.<br><br>
Aside from one boyhood friend, none of my friends I had before Vietnam or after, ever served in the military. They have ALWAYS respected my decision to go and I have certainly respected the fact that they never served. There is no way I would ever change places.<br><br>
I never was one to get into pissing contests with people.<br><br>
I have disagreed, yet never have I shown disrespect for opposing points of view concerning the war. I have disagreed but not out of intolerance. I have great respect for those who fought in Vietnam and feel the war was *justified*. They put their asses on the line for what they believed. They deserve respect also.<br><br>
If you truly want to learn, that is fine. Everyone needs to learn, and *should* learn.<br><br>
Respect should come first. Respect doesn't mean agreement. Respect involves being tactful and unassuming. State your opinions and in the words of Art Varinelli, &quot;Judge No one&quot;.<br><br>
Don't ever kid yourself that you were the voice in anyone's ear. <br>

<p><code>-- wingman@greene.xtn.net  (Tom Dier) </code><p>


